.TH "cpufreq_update_policy" 9 "cpufreq_update_policy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpufreq_update_policy \- Re-evaluate an existing cpufreq policy.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cpufreq_update_policy
.BI "(unsigned int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
CPU to re-evaluate the policy for.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the current frequency for the cpufreq policy of \fIcpu\fP and use
\fBcpufreq_set_policy\fP to re-apply the min and max limits, which triggers the
evaluation of policy notifiers and the cpufreq driver's ->\fBverify\fP callback
for the policy in question, among other things.
